%N A337117 Spiral on a 2D square lattice, one term per cell, starting at the origin with 0; the four integers forming any 2 X 2 square add up to a palindrome.
%C A337117 This is the lexicographically earliest permutation of the nonnegative integers with this property.
%H A337117 Jean-Marc Falcoz, <a href="/A337117/b337117.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2757</a>
%e A337117 The four integers inside each of the four 2 X 2 squares that contain 0 sum up to a palindrome: 0+1+2+3=6 / 0+3+4+15=22 / 0+15+5+13=33 / 0+13+8+1=22. This is true for any 2 X 2 square picked up on the (infinite) grid: the upper right corner below sums up to 88 for instance (17+22+43+6).
